  "prompt": "How do you write a thesis statement on capital punishment?",
  "response": "Writing a thesis statement on capital punishment involves clearly presenting your position on the issue. Here are some steps to help you construct a strong thesis statement:\n\n1. **Choose Your Stance:**\n   Decide whether you are for or against capital punishment. Your thesis should reflect your central argument or viewpoint.\n\n2. **Narrow Down Your Focus:**\n   Identify specific aspects of capital punishment you will address, such as its morality, effectiveness as a deterrent, cost implications, or impact on society.\n\n3. **Make It Debatable:**\n   Ensure your thesis statement presents an argument that can be challenged or opposed. Avoid statements of fact and aim for those that can ignite discussion.\n\n4. **Be Specific:**\n   Your thesis should be clear and specific enough to guide the direction of your paper. It should hint at the main points you will discuss to support your stance.\n\nHere are examples of thesis statements on capital punishment:\n\n1. **Against Capital Punishment:**\n   \"Capital punishment is an inhumane and ineffective means of achieving justice, failing as a deterrent to crime and perpetuating systemic biases in the legal system.\"\n\n2. **For Capital Punishment:**\n   \"The death penalty serves as a necessary and justified measure for the most heinous crimes, providing a deterrent effect that protects society and delivers justice for victims.\"\n\n3. **Economic Perspective:**\n   \"Contrary to popular belief, capital punishment imposes a higher financial burden on taxpayers compared to life imprisonment without parole, due to the extensive legal processes required.\"\n\n4. **Moral Perspective:**\n   \"Capital punishment violates fundamental human rights and moral principles, as it represents the irreversible and ultimate denial of the possibility for rehabilitation and redemption.\"\n\nChoose the angle that best fits your research and arguments, and craft a thesis statement that encapsulates your position succinctly.",
